<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title></title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Written submission from the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">London Fire and Emergency Planning Authority (BRC 67)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">1.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The London Fire and Emergency Planning Authority</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> (LFEPA)</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> run the London Fire Brigade</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> (LFB)</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> and is a functional body of the Greater London Authority. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">London’s fire and rescue service is the busiest in the country and one of the largest firefighting and rescue organisations in the world. We provide services acro</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ss the whole of the Greater London area, serving London’s 8.2 million residents as well as those who work in or visit the city.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">2.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Around 6,500 staff work for the Brigade. This includes over 5,500 operational firefighters, 100 Brigade Control staff dealin</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">g with 999 emergency calls and a range of non-operational staff working behind the scenes to deliver support services such as getting fire safety messages across.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">3.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The LFB</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> has reviewed its data relating to domestic fires resulting from electrical causes</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> (not including white goods/portable appliances) and does not have substantive evidence of an increased risk of fire or danger to the public, due to the operation of the electrical competent persons scheme.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">4.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">However, the LFB does has significant concern</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> regarding a closely related issue, which is that of on-going electrical safety inspections in rented domestic accommodation. Unlike the Gas Safety (Installation and Use) Regulations 1998, where landlords have a duty (annually) to make sure gas appliances,</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> fittings and flues provided for tenants are safe, there is currently no statutory requirement to have annual safety checks carried out on the electrical installation or electrical equipment.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">5.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Through the work of the Brigade’s fire investigation team, s</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ignificant qualitative data has been accumulated which shows that serious fires have occurred due to dangerous and untested electrical installations in rented properties. Cases involving extensive property damage and even fatalities have been recorded. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Th</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">e LFB would be happy to provide detailed evidence to support the need for change and ask </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">D</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">CLG to consider making annual landlords electrical safety checks </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">(and ideally portable appliance testing) mandatory, to either match the Gas Safety (Installation and </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Use) Regulations 1998, or else to take place at reasonable intervals e.g. 1-3 years.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">6.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">In support of this submission, please see a </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">report</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">- entitled ‘</span><a href="http://moderngov.london-fire.gov.uk/ieListDocuments.aspx?CId=145&amp;MId=230&amp;Ver=4"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">Thematic Rep</span><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">ort on Electrical Fires</span><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline"> (</span><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">FEP 1953</span><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">)</span></a><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">’ - which can be found on the London Fire website and </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">which was agreed</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> at the LFEPA</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">’s Strategy Committee</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">.  The report</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> looks at the occurrence of accidental dwelling </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">fires where the source of ignition is powered by elect</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ricity.  The report also highlights the prevention work undertaken both to change human behaviours and work to improve electrical supply and appliance design. </span><a name="_GoBack"></a></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">December 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>